    "description": "The orthogonality regularization follow-up regressed on both proxy FVU and throughput, so more local regularization sweeps are not justified. This round adds a new `union_topk` family under `sparsify/` and tests it first at the same K=128/ef=8/Adam anchor, probing whether branch-level candidate union is a better way to add encoder expressivity than the recent additive, gating, or suppression mechanisms.",
